T1  - Monetarism and the US economy: A re-evaluation of Stein's model 1960–1973
AU  - Desai, Meghnad
AU  - Blake, David
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 10
IS  - 1
SP  - 111
EP  - 125
PY  - 1982
DA  - 1982/07/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0304-3932(82)80008-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304393282800081
AB  - We take a small macroeconomic model, due to Stein, designed to capture the essential aspects of Keynesian and monetarist propositions, especially on the question of crowding out. We show that Stein's empirical procedure is inadequate: he ignores the restrictions that he imposed on the structure of his model and concentrates on single equation reduced form estimation. We are able to derive complete maximum likelihood estimates of the structural parameters subject to the non-linear restrictions of the model. Using identical data and the same specifications but with these more appropriate estimation techniques, we show that conclusions opposite to those of Stein may be reached.
